          "TITLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "-Neutron scattering lengths of molten metals determined",
                " by gravity refractometry."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "AUTHOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "G.Reiner",
                "W.Waschkowski",
                "L.Koester"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INSTITUTE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "2GERMUN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "REAC"
                ],
                "institute": "2GERMUN"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Frm open pool research reactor."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "REAC"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                "  Neutron-gravity-refractometer using 108 m",
                " flight path with a drop in height of up to 1.8 m."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "REFL"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Neutron-gravity-refractometer. The reflectivity",
                " (reflected/incident neutron numbers) of a liquid",
                " mirror of the molten metal sample was measured as a",
                " function of the geometric height fall of the neutron",
                " beam."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".The measured reflectivities against height fall are",
                " fitted by a reflection curve, from which the point of",
                " total reflection is obtained occurring at the critical",
                " height fall for the metal. The coherent scattering",
                " length for bound atoms is proportional to this",
                " critical height fall."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ASSUMED": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".The constant of proportionality between the critical",
                " height fall and the coherent scattering length is",
                " calculated using the following assumed values:",
                "         neutron mass = 939.5720(42) MeV/C2",
                "             little g = 9.80745(10) m/S2",
                "     planck'S const H = 6.582122(39)e-22 MeV.S",
                "                    l = 6.0221367(36)e+23 1/mol"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "BF3"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "   Length 1 m, diameter 5 cm."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "PART-DET": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "N"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".Liquid metal mirrors of better than 99.99% purity and",
                " dimensions of 60 X 40 cm2, housed in a cylindrical",
                " vacuum chamber 110 cm long and 50 cm in diam. Quartz-",
                " glass windows in the cylinder ends allowed the broad",
                " 40 cm neutron beam to traverse the chamber."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-T",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Total error about 0.03 %. The systematic error",
                " is an order of magnitude smaller."
              ]
